column5: Looking at the Barrie live cams it looks to have started.  The image it pretty grainy anyone in the area confirm?  How's oro doing?
NICE.  If Kemp is starting to lock up, then the rest of the lake should be starting to be in good shape!
Won't be anytime soon out to the laker grounds that's for sure but if it is skim and we can keep it for the next few days its encouraging
Skim with 45km/h winds today?  I'd be surprised if there is any ice at all on the bay.
I was thinking the same Bill.  If there was any, it's now in Beaverton.
I'm just talking right downtown at minuets pt.  and the marina.  Look at the live camera. I didn't believe it either but it damn sure looks like ice.  anyone actually live nearby had a look?
I'll take a drive by tonight and check it out.  If there was any ice starting to form in the bay, that's all been blown down towards the marina/ramp.  Maybe that's what you're seeing.
http://www.barrie.ca/City%20Hall/Webcams/Pages/default.aspx   Yea, it looks iced over.  I wouldn't dare walk on it any time soon but I will take what I can get.
Ok I will look on my way over to the bakery.. I know they are fishing in the marina.  Yes it does look skimed in the pic.

I was there yesterday afternoon and it had not even frozen out past the inner breakwall and there were a lot of wet patches inside the inner harbour.  If it's freezing at this temp with 45km/h wind gusts then science has just been turned on its head.
That will be $2.50 for the fuel.
I'll pay for that fuel as it saved me about $60 for the round trip.
Needed buns for the homemade meatball subs.$2.50 was the cost of the buns.LOL  Dec 3rd Not my photo. http://rstorage.filemobile.com/storage/9339652/1085
Lol . My dreams are shattered.    I'm headed up to Dorset in about 6 hours
Be thankful.....we might have had to change your name to "Lastrax". Have a great season and please be cautious always but especially at the start and end of the season.
